â”‚ DECISION: Server Components + Server Actions (NOT REST API routes)                       â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¤
â”‚                                                                                          â”‚
â”‚   For Next.js 16 with Supabase, we use:                                                 â”‚
â”‚                                                                                          â”‚
â”‚   READS:   Direct Supabase queries in Server Components                                 â”‚
â”‚            - No /api/ routes needed for page data                                       â”‚
â”‚            - Query directly in page.tsx with server-side auth                           â”‚
â”‚            - Reusable query functions in lib/queries/*.ts                               â”‚
â”‚                                                                                          â”‚
â”‚   WRITES:  Server Actions in lib/actions/*.ts                                           â”‚
â”‚            - "use server" directive                                                      â”‚
â”‚            - Called from client components via form actions or direct calls             â”‚
â”‚            - Use revalidatePath() after mutations                                       â”‚
â”‚                                                                                          â”‚
â”‚   EXCEPTIONS (where API routes ARE needed):                                             â”‚
â”‚            - External/mobile API access (future)                                        â”‚
â”‚            - Webhook endpoints (Stripe, etc.)                                           â”‚
â”‚            - Long-polling or streaming endpoints                                        â”‚
â”‚                                                                                          â”‚
â”‚   This eliminates redundant API routes and aligns with Next.js best practices.          â”‚
â”‚                                                                                          â”‚
